如今迷失在威尔士🏴󠁧󠁢󠁷󠁬󠁳󠁿</description><language>zh-CN</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 09:56:44 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title/><link>https://pixelfed.social/p/Jess.Stetson/971889550839014614</link><description>&lt;img alt="A view of Cnicht mountain at sunrise from a street in Porthmadog, North Wales. An empty asphalt road with bright double yellow lines on either side stretches far ahead. Traditional stone and slate-roofed buildings line both sides of the street. In the distance, the sharp, triangular silhouette of the mountain Cnicht rises against a brilliant sky filled with orange, yellow, and blue clouds." referrerpolicy="no-referrer" src="https://pxscdn.com/public/m/_v2/787879165920376064/b5862bd14-4506fa/V7dYWoSctaX4/9Ye18rvaUZAaJI2lmwV7x4EsuIfSbqMUrCpG5CmN.jpg"/&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://pixelfed.social/p/Jess.Stetson/971862412600096257</link><description>&lt;img alt="The dimly lit interior of the historic Besse-Marrel burial vault located in Père-Lachaise Cemetery. A severely decayed cast-iron bust of a woman sits in a central oval with small holes having been eaten away on her face over time. The bust is flanked by two stone inscription plaques; the darker one on the left is mostly illegible, while the right plaque clearly reads &amp;quot;ANNE MARIE BRIGITTE MARREL / VEUVE BESSE / DÉCÉDÉE LE 11 MAI 1866 / À L'ÂGE DE 73 ANS&amp;quot; (translated: Anne Marie Brigitte Marrel, widow of Besse, deceased May 11, 1866, at the age of 73 years). Vertical rusted metal rods line the walls to either side of the bust and fallen leaves litter the stone graves below. A dried wreath rests on the floor while a bouquet of old yet still bright artificial flowers provide a burst of colour just to the left of the bust." referrerpolicy="no-referrer" src="https://pxscdn.com/public/m/_v2/787879165920376064/b5862bd14-4506fa/nm0cdtl8Jps7/vDcBsHT8Bddl2yUd3CcB5f38skzRQdFwqs1IUTM3.jpg"/&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://pixelfed.social/p/Jess.Stetson/971780920852546985</link><description>&lt;img alt="A close-up shot of a thick blanket of vibrant green feather moss covering a tree trunk. The texture of the moss is highly detailed in the foreground, showing soft, intricate fronds. In the blurred background, a bare tree branch is silhouetted against a blue sky with light clouds." referrerpolicy="no-referrer" src="https://pxscdn.com/public/m/_v2/787879165920376064/b5862bd14-4506fa/b0NYHKvHlwsG/XtSHhSre7XRIFOZfuSC47CIJiyS4WJSw3H1dEGez.jpg"/&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://pixelfed.social/p/Jess.Stetson/971764317270080937</link><description>&lt;img alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" src="https://pxscdn.com/public/m/_v2/787879165920376064/b5862bd14-4506fa/OrrfHlDMbgTx/x6p4B7HnuPhgUcVgt3VjVid7FXjWpBYWzxe9xO86.jpg"/&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://pixelfed.social/p/Jess.Stetson/971636980841491419</link><description>&lt;img alt="A view over Porthmadog Harbour during a vibrant golden sunrise. Boats are moored at docks, and anchored in the harbour waters, their reflections visible on the calm water. In the background, the dark, dramatic silhouettes of the Moelwynion mountain range, including the pointed peak of Cnicht, stand against an orange and blue sky streaked with light clouds." referrerpolicy="no-referrer" src="https://pxscdn.com/public/m/_v2/787879165920376064/b5862bd14-4506fa/LnDPtaEZMrDc/ICsrI0AkY2HGSa9YJCy0FNhdvzH2mSzWk6PHB9Q2.jpg"/&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>